data.text:
In the West Bank and Gaza, USAID empowers Palestinians to build thriving communities, promote inclusive development and advance a two-state solution. USAID assistance aims to increase stability and improve lives by working within local communities to increase economic opportunity and access to basic services, promote effective governance, empower youth, and provide humanitarian relief. Additionally, USAID strives to build trust, mutual understanding, and respect by advancing cooperation between Israelis and Palestinians through its peacebuilding initiatives. USAIDâ€™s assistance helps build a freer, more prosperous, and more secure region, benefiting Palestinians, Israelis, and Americans.

Mission Director Amy Tohill-Stull
